# Plane CLI Reference

Auto-generated on {{ .Generated }}. {{ .Total }} actions across {{ len .Topics }} resource types.

## Quick Start

```bash
# Create a work item
plane issue create --name "Fix login bug" --state "In Progress" --priority urgent -w my-workspace -p MY-PROJECT

# List all cycles
plane cycle list -w my-workspace -p MY-PROJECT

# Idempotent upsert (ensure)
plane label ensure --name "backend" --color "#00FF00" -w my-workspace -p MY-PROJECT

# Batch create from JSONL
echo '{"name":"Task 1"}
{"name":"Task 2"}' | plane issue create --batch -w my-workspace -p MY-PROJECT

# Extract a single field
plane issue get --work-item-id PROJ-42 --field state_detail.name -w my-workspace -p MY-PROJECT
```

## Agent Features

### Name Resolution
Flags that accept UUIDs also accept human-readable names. The CLI resolves names to UUIDs automatically.
- `--state-id "In Progress"` resolves the state name to its UUID
- `--label-id backend` resolves the label name to its UUID
- `--work-item-id PROJ-42` resolves the sequence ID to a UUID

Disable with `--no-resolve` to pass literal values.

### Output Extraction
- `--field <path>` — extract a single field (supports dotted paths like `state_detail.name`)
- `--fields <a,b,c>` — extract multiple fields as TSV
- `--id-only` — print only the resource UUID
- `--output json` or `--output table` — force output format

### Ensure (Idempotent Upsert)
Topics that support ensure will create-or-update a resource by name:
```bash
plane <topic> ensure --name "value" [--other-flags...]
```
If a resource with that name exists, it is updated. Otherwise, it is created.

### Batch Mode
Read JSONL from stdin; each line becomes a separate API request:
```bash
cat items.jsonl | plane <topic> create --batch -w my-workspace -p MY-PROJECT
```

### Dry Run
Preview the HTTP request without executing:
```bash
plane issue create --name "test" --dry-run -w my-workspace -p MY-PROJECT
```

### Pagination
- `--per-page N` — items per page (max 100, default 100)
- `--cursor <token>` — resume from a pagination cursor
- `--all` — auto-paginate and return all results

